{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fc18571d-89d0-4727-8e1a-0299a7bc49c5","content":"Here's how to set up **NuGet Trusted Publishing** using GitHub Actions OIDC — no API keys stored anywhere:\n\n## 1. Configure nuget.org\n\n1. Sign in to [nuget.org](https://nuget.org) → **Account Settings** → **Trusted Publishers**\n2. Add a new trusted publisher:\n   - **Repository owner:** `myorg`\n   - **Repository name:** `mylib`\n   - **Workflow file:** `publish.yml`\n   - **Environment:** `nuget-publish` *(recommended)*\n\n## 2. Create a GitHub Environment\n\nIn your repo → **Settings** → **Environments** → create `nuget-publish`. Add protection rules (e.g., require approval, restrict to `v*` tags).\n\n## 3. Create the workflow\n\n`.github/workflows/publish.yml`:\n\n```yaml\nname: Publish to NuGet\n\non:\n  push:\n    tags: ['v*']\n\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    environment: nuget-publish          # must match nuget.org config\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write                   # request OIDC token\n      contents: read\n\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      - uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4\n        with:\n          dotnet-version: '8.0.x'\n\n      - run: dotnet pack src/MyLib/MyLib.csproj -c Release -o ./artifacts\n\n      - name: Publish to NuGet (trusted publishing)\n        run: |\n          dotnet nuget push ./artifacts/*.nupkg \\\n            --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n## How it works\n\n| Concept | Detail |\n|---|---|\n| **OIDC token** | GitHub mints a short-lived JWT proving the workflow identity |\n| **Trusted publisher** | nuget.org verifies the token matches your repo/workflow/environment |\n| **No secrets** | No API key to rotate, leak, or store — the trust is in the identity |\n\n## Release flow\n\n```bash\ngit tag v1.0.0\ngit push origin v1.0.0\n```\n\nThe tag push triggers the workflow, which authenticates via OIDC and publishes automatically.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d47d6f5a-4f7a-473e-ac28-613eb7784e80","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to set up secure NuGet publishing from GitHub Actions using trusted publishing (without API keys). This is a knowledge/guidance question - I don't need to explore any codebase. Let me provide a concise but complete answer.\n\nThe modern approach is to use NuGet's trusted publishing with OIDC tokens, which was introduced in 2024. This avoids storing API keys as secrets.\n\nLet me outline the steps:\n\n1. Register the package on nuget.org and configure trusted publishing (GitHub Actions OIDC)\n2. Create a GitHub Actions workflow that uses OIDC to authenticate\n\nActually, NuGet.org supports trusted publishing now. Let me give the accurate setup.\n\n\nThe process mirrors PyPI's trusted publishing model. On nuget.org, I configure the package to trust OIDC tokens from a specific GitHub Actions workflow. When the workflow runs, it requests an OIDC token from GitHub, exchanges it with nuget.org for a temporary API key, then uses that key to push the package. the NuGet API to get an actual key, then use `dotnet nuget push` with that key against the official NuGet source. The exact flow involves setting `permissions: id-token: write` in the GitHub Actions job, exchanging the OIDC token for a NuGet credential, and pushing the package with that credential. I'm working through the specifics of how to set this up securely as a recommended approach.\n\nSetting up NuGet Trusted Publishing... → Trusted publishers section where I specify the GitHub repository details and workflow file. Then in the GitHub Actions workflow itself, I need to set `permissions: id-token: write` so the workflow can request an OIDC token. The `dotnet nuget push` command should work without an explicit API key since the trusted publishing setup handles the token exchange automatically—GitHub provides the OIDC token, nuget.org validates it and grants temporary access, and the push completes without storing any permanent credentials.","outputTokens":2081,"requestId":"242A:3835CB:1622783:18B42BB:6A051EA4"},"id":"6951bcea-5d58-4a8c-8c2d-3846e59a5d90","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:00:57.619Z","parentId":"7a2e8246-e598-452c-8bd9-75c0f0ede924"}
